<br>
If you ever have played a monk, you know that you can train two mobs on eachother, (sarnak and gob in LOIO) let them beat eachother up, and then when the sarnak kills the gob, you immediately pop up out of FD and kill the sarnak, even if it only takes one hit to kill it, you still get full exp, because the agro was stopped by the sarnak killing the gob.  When agro is erased, the system resets at the mobs CURRENT hps, and gains as the mob gains in health.   If you try to kill the sarnak while he is still fighting the gob, you will find yourself fighting two mobs, and will also find that you will only get exp on one of the two kills, the last one.  <br>
<br>
IF mobs are still fighting eachother, you have to do TWO things to get the kill, over 51% dmg, AND the kill shot.  (I used to do this with my druid, training giants-captain especially, from the giant fort in East Wastes, over to the dwarfs, I would unload enough DD's on it to get it to half health, then train him over the dwarfs and let them do the other half of dmg, then would save enough mana to get the kill shot, viola, I get the exp).  But, if agro with the two mobs has been cleared (including the agro on yourself--ie, FD), by one of them dying, then agro is reset REGARDLESS of the health of the mob, and you only need to kill it regardless of its health to get the exp. <br>
<br>
In other words, you DONT have to wait till a mob gets back up to 51% health to get exp on the kill, so WHY would you have to wait for a PC to get back up to 51%.  <br>
<br>
